<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2648: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Provisional President <persName type="from">Burgos</persName> to President <persName type="to">Harding</persName></hi><note n="50" xml:id="d62fn50">A similar
                                telegram, undated, was received by the Department Oct. 30, 1922,
                                from the Dominican Commissioners—Archbishop Nouel, Horacio Vasquez,
                                Federico Velasquez, E. Brache, Francisco J. Peynado (file no.
                                839.00/2647).</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I should be pleased if, for the sake of the success of the liberation
                            plan, the mission of the Honorable Sumner Welles should not terminate
                            before the inauguration of the Constitutional President.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Vicini
                            Burgos</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>